-- Paladin Plans to Spend $292 Million Building Schools, Business Day Reports
-- B y   A n a   M o n t e i r o
-- 2010-10-13T05:37:59Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-13/paladin-plans-to-spend-292-million-building-schools-business-day-reports.html
Paladin Capital Ltd., a private-
equity company, plans to spend 2 billion rand ($292 million)over
the next 10 years building schools in parts of South Africa,
Business Day reported, citing Chief Executive Officer Francois
Swart.   The company owns 76 percent of Curro Holdings, a private-
school group that has five schools with 3,090 students, which
plans to expand to as many as 40 schools in the next decade, the
Johannesburg-based newspaper cited Swart as saying.   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Ana Monteiro at 
 amonteiro4@bloomberg.net  